1
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:23,920
I've been streaming lately.

2
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:25,840
Wow.

3
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:28,480
Okay, I'll sing a song for you.

4
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:30,280
Is it that difficult?

5
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:32,400
This outfit?

6
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:34,840
Oh, this outfit is provided by the manufacturer.

7
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:36,280
If you need it,

8
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,200
I can give you the link.

9
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,880
Use topics to bring traffic into the stream.

10
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:47,760
It's been more than ten days since she started streaming.

11
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:48,620
Manager Huang.

12
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:50,160
Only seven thousand followers.

13
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:50,720
Oh.

14
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:52,520
What use is a student?

15
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:54,000
It's a waste of company resources.

16
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,160
You never know.

17
00:00:55,360 --> 00:00:55,800
What?

18
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,780
I watch a lot of streams every day,

19
00:00:57,920 --> 00:00:59,120
and there aren't many people who gain followers

20
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:00,000
as fast as she does.

21
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:00,760
Tch.

22
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:02,880
She streams for eight hours a day.

23
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:03,880
Every time slot is different.

24
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:06,200
I'm asking you, are you done with your work?

25
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:06,800
Oh.

26
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:07,840
Almost done.

27
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,760
Then get to it.

28
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:13,560
Humph.

29
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,120
Ignorant.

30
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,460
I'm logging off for today.

31
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:23,580
See you all tomorrow on time, babies.

32
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:34,560
The warm-up for today is done too.

33
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,160
Yeah.

34
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:37,400
The follower growth during the day was still a bit slow.

35
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:38,000
Yeah.

36
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,880
The platform will start an esports competition tonight.

37
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,680
I saved up some streaming coupons.

38
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,240
Taking advantage of this event,

39
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:45,840
we should be able to break

40
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:53,200
10,000 followers.

41
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,720
Yang Qian.

42
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:05,520
Why hasn't Zixi been coming to class lately?

43
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:06,680
Is she sick?

44
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:07,800
No.

45
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:09,960
She's been busy with live streaming lately.

46
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,880
Live streaming?

47
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:11,520
Yeah.

48
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,520
She's quite busy.

49
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:15,560
She's already applied to change her class schedule.

50
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,120
She's changing her schedule?

51
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,720
I can't reschedule your classes anymore.

52
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,320
If you keep rescheduling like this,

53
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,040
you won't have to attend school at all this semester.

54
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:23,920
Professor.

55
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:26,520
My startup is at a critical stage right now.

56
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,360
Please help me out.

57
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:30,840
I know the school encourages you to do

58
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:31,960
on-campus startups.

59
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,640
But this is going too far.

60
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,600
I know.

61
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:38,640
I promise I'll make up for the classes after you reschedule them.

62
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,770
Please, Professor.

63
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,180
For these courses,

64
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,720
the best I can do is excuse your attendance.

65
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:46,960
If you study on your own and pass the exams...

66
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,040
I'll consider you passed.

67
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:48,560
Okay.

68
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,079
Mhm.

69
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:51,880
Thank you, teacher.

70
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:52,400
Go on.

71
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,240
If you can help her earn 300,000,

72
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:03,290
I'll help you get back to the group.

73
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,040
Auntie is so pretty.

74
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,360
How did it go?

75
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,480
It went pretty smoothly.

76
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,520
The teacher agreed to reschedule the class.

77
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,579
Not rescheduling.

78
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,960
The teacher said as long as I pass the exam,

79
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:22,090
my attendance score won't be counted.

80
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,240
So that means no.

81
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,079
No.

82
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:28,320
I just need to find more time to study between livestreams.

83
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,680
Let's pause for a while.

84
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,720
Why?

85
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,880
You've been streaming continuously for so long,

86
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:35,160
you should take a break.

87
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:35,960
No.

88
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:38,760
Stopping now means all our previous efforts will be in vain.

89
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,360
There are only 24 hours in a day.

90
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,640
Even a machine needs to rest.

91
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:45,100
If we give up now, doesn't it mean your efforts are also wasted?

92
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,160
I...

93
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,760
For every livestream, you have to select products and write scripts.

94
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:52,640
Afterward, you have to review and coordinate with companies.

95
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,680
Are you willing to give up now?

96
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:58,360
Don't you want to meet the target ASAP and see your family?

97
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,240
Okay.

98
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,200
Don't worry.

99
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:03,040
I'm fine.

100
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,440
For the esports match tonight,

101
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,640
wearing this outfit,

102
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:12,770
how does it look?

103
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,320
Looks good.

104
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:21,480
Ahao,

105
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:23,770
do you usually watch live streams?

106
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:24,960
Of course I do.

107
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:28,770
There's a really popular esports match on a platform recently.

108
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:30,720
Then,

109
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,240
have you come across Yin Zixi?

110
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,400
Yin Zixi?

111
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,320
No.

112
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,200
Oh.

113
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:41,060
No wonder I haven't seen her in class lately.

114
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,320
If she changes her class schedule,

115
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:47,120
I'll see her even less.

116
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,480
What's wrong?

117
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,370
I can't fasten this.

118
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:56,900
Let me do it.

119
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,160
Done.

120
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,000
All right.

121
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,250
How is it?

122
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,580
Are you confident?

123
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,760
Just watch me.

124
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:26,680
What?

125
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:27,640
A female player.

126
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,640
A streamer can actually play games?

127
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,720
Even though I'm not a gaming streamer,

128
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,400
at least

129
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:35,420
I've been playing seven years longer than you guys.

130
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,290
You watch game streams too?

131
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:41,760
No.

132
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,080
I saw our classmate.

133
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,159
Our classmate?

134
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:44,680
Yes.

135
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:45,480
Look.

136
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:48,560
Doesn't this look like our classmate Yin Zixi?

137
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:50,000
Yin Zixi?

138
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,320
It really is her.

139
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,580
Playing Vanguard.

140
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,880
Is this Yin Zixi?

141
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,360
How did she sneak into Group A?

142
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:02,680
Hey.

143
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,400
She played the new hero quite well last match.

144
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,320
Really?

145
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:11,300
I'll push the lane first, you guys fight.

146
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:14,480
The enemy is attacking the Baron.

147
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,680
Check it out quickly.

148
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:18,480
The Baron.

149
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:24,040
Ah.

150
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,760
We finally won.

151
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,480
Are you a professional player, streamer?

152
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,840
I'm not.

153
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:30,640
I just came to get some popularity.

154
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,840
I'm just here for the clout.

155
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,120
You're about to enter the top 16.

156
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,480
And you're not even a gaming streamer.

157
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,080
Yeah.

158
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:37,480
I didn't expect it to go so smoothly either.

159
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:40,680
Congratulations to Donghai 183

160
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:41,840
for becoming the

161
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,200
10,000th fan in our stream.

162
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,260
Congratulations.

163
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:48,560
Hello.

164
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,120
Lucky fan,

165
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,380
do you have any wishes?

166
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,240
Of course I do.

167
00:06:57,520 --> 00:07:00,400
Let me think about it.

168
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,400
Then you'd better think fast.

169
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,280
We won't wait if time runs out.

170
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:15,680
All right.

171
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,400
Babes,

172
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,920
today's live stream is over.

173
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,080
See you tomorrow.

174
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:19,920
Bye-bye.

175
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,060
Why did you end the broadcast so early today?

176
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,160
Congratulations.

177
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,560
You hit the target early.

178
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,240
Wow.

179
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,800
But doesn't this break

180
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,400
our broadcasting schedule?

181
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,080
Yes.

182
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:39,200
From now on, we'll stream for six hours a day.

183
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,000
Why?

184
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,200
With such long streams,

185
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,200
even if you can keep going,

186
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,640
the audience will get bored.

187
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:46,280
We already have enough regular fans.

188
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:48,320
Let's concentrate our time a bit more.

189
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,400
But tonight ended

190
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,060
a bit too abruptly, didn't it?

191
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:52,540
Tomorrow is the top 16.

192
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,400
You need a good rest tonight.

193
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:56,200
Don't disappoint your new fans.

194
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:57,280
Yeah.

195
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,200
Hey, stop zoning out.

196
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,120
Come help me.

197
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,000
Oh.

198
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:17,160
Hey.

199
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,320
Haven't you already finished?

200
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:34,799
Hello.

201
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:35,919
Is this Yin Zixi?

202
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:36,919
You have a delivery.

203
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:38,360
Please come out and sign for it.

204
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,799
Okay, coming.

205
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,520
Why didn't I

206
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,880
save An Yufan's phone number?

207
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,120
Zixi.

208
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:55,560
Let me help you.

209
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,320
Oh, no need.

210
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,600
I can do it myself.

211
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:59,760
I have something else to give you.

212
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:03,760
It's fine.

213
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,400
What is this?

214
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,560
This is...

215
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,080
Where

216
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,720
are we going?

217
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,120
This...

218
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:15,360
I'll help you.

219
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:31,400
Hey, which page is this news comment on?

220
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,560
Let me see.

221
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,080
Oh.

222
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,120
This?

223
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,840
The teacher improvised this based on current events.

224
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,840
I was afraid the teacher would test us on current events,

225
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,560
so I wrote them down.

226
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,920
There are even extracurricular topics.

227
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:46,440
Yeah.

228
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:47,900
Thank you, Liang Chen.

229
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:48,900
No problem.

230
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:52,040
I heard the teacher refused to reschedule your class.

231
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,240
I thought you might need it,

232
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,370
so I took some notes.

233
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,440
Sorry to trouble you.

234
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:00,320
I'll head back now.

235
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:01,520
Study well.

236
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:02,200
Okay.

237
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,360
Bye.

238
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:04,320
Bye, Zixi.

239
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:32,640
Assistant Casting Director Xi Chongjing

240
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,520
Props Assistant Li Kunxiao

241
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:36,480
Production Vehicle Yi Mingle

242
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:38,400
Yitong
